Program: Discovery
Title: Super volcanoes
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryk6
Last Broadcast Date: 03 December 2003
Is there a super volcano beneath Yellowstone National Park? Under the park lies a sleeping giant which could have devastating consequences if it woke. It would eject so much ash that nearby cities would be under kilometers of ash. The amount of material put into the atmosphere could cause many on earth to perish. Show less